Edison Pebojot

Edison Nacional Pebojot (/ˈpəʌbo|jo:tː/) is a software developer. Pebojot was raised in the Philippines and attended AMA Computer University. Pebojot has also attended St. Patrick’s Academy Inc., a Catholic high school. After two years, he went to Science High School in Surigao Del Sur, Philippines, where he studied Physics. [Encyclopedia]


Born: Dingalan, Aurora, Philippines

Education: AMA Computer University (BS)

Occupation: Google Play Developer, Software Developer

  • Describe Your Task as a Software Developer
  • The Basics of Software Requirement Gathering
  • Muon: Software Package Directory
  • Software Ethics to me (or to you)
  • An Android Platform for Filipino Employment (Beta Program)
  • www.pebojot.com
  • The Vacuum Project
  • Elliptic Curve Cryptography and Quantum Computing: The Mathematics
  • Braindotnet
  • Hackathon Event: AMA Computer University
  • Tree Planting: About Environmental Conservation
  • Theatre: Acting Session for El Filibusterismo in Grade 10
